verses.text:
If I be wicked, woe unto me; and
if I be righteous,
yet will I not lift up my head.
I am full of confusion; therefore see thou mine affliction;

Before I go
whence I shall not return,
even to the land of darkness and the shadow of death;

Seeing his days
are determined, the number of his months
are with thee, thou hast appointed his bounds that he cannot pass;

Because he hath oppressed
and hath forsaken the poor;
because he hath violently taken away an house which he builded not;

They cause
him to go naked without clothing, and they take away the sheaf
from the hungry;

As God liveth,
who hath taken away my judgment; and the Almighty,
who hath vexed my soul;

All the while my breath
is in me, and the spirit of God
is in my nostrils;

The flood breaketh out from the inhabitant;
even the waters
 forgotten of the foot: they are dried up, they are gone away from men.

When his candle shined upon my head,
and when by his light I walked
through darkness;

As I was in the days of my youth, when the secret of God
was
 upon my tabernacle;

If I beheld the sun when it shined, or the moon walking
in
 brightness;

He looketh upon men, and
if any say, I have sinned, and perverted
that which was right, and it profited me not;

And if
they be bound in fetters,
and be holden in cords of affliction;

Teach us what we shall say unto him;
for we cannot order
our speech by reason of darkness.

She is hardened against her young ones, as though
they were
 not hers: her labour is in vain without fear;

He maketh a path to shine after him;
one would think the deep
to be hoary.
